'''配體門控離子通道'''（Ligand-gated ion channel,LICs, LGIC）又稱為'''離子受體'''（ionotropic receptors），是一組[[跨膜蛋白|跨膜]][[離子通道|離子通道]]蛋白，可打開以響應諸如化學信使（即[[配體|配體]]，例如[[神經傳遞物質|神經傳遞物質]])的結合而允許諸如 Na+, K+, Ca2+和/或Cl−離子通過[[細胞膜|細胞膜]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.genenames.org/cgi-bin/genefamilies/set/161|title=Gene Family: Ligand gated ion channels|publisher=HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee|access-date=2020-10-14|archive-date=2017-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171114202400/https://www.genenames.org/cgi-bin/genefamilies/set/161|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{DorlandsDict|two/000019817|ligand-gated channel}}</ref><ref name="Purves" >{{cite book | author = Purves, Dale, George J. Augustine, David Fitzpatrick, William C. Hall, Anthony-Samuel LaMantia, James O. McNamara, and Leonard E. White | title = Neuroscience. 4th ed. | url = https://archive.org/details/neuroscienceissu00purv | publisher = Sinauer Associates | pages = [https://archive.org/details/neuroscienceissu00purv/page/n181 156]–7 | year = 2008 | isbn = 978-0-87893-697-7}}</ref>

當突觸前神經元興奮時，它會從[[囊泡|囊泡]]向突觸間隙釋放[[神經遞質|神經遞質]]。然後，神經遞質與突觸後神經元上的受體結合。如果這些受體是配體閘門離子通道，則發生的構象變化會打開離子通道，從而導致離子流過細胞膜。反過來，這導致於興奮性受體反應時[[去極化|去極化]]或於抑制反應時[[超极化_(生物学)|超極化]]。

